htbox-0"><img src="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/bitcoin.png" alt="bitcoin" width="102" height="64" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-8639" /></a>A small bug currently in how AdRotate blocks work affects a number of people. This is most likely due to a sizing issue from the outer div element. This is being investigated and a patch is being tested.<br />\nThe issue at hand is that blocks with multiple columns are cut off too early. So a 3 column block gets only 2 columns, etc.</p>\n<p>Another, yet again, glaring issue is that my Bank (Yes that&#8217;s you Rabobank!) yet again seems unable to process Credit Card payments. A solution from them is *not* forthcoming. In fact, they&#8217;ve stopped talking to me about it. Which means they don&#8217;t give a damn. I&#8217;m looking into the issue and am trying to get a new payment processor online as soon as possible. But for now Credit Cards are not accepted.</p>\n<p>On a more cheery note, I&#8217;ve jumped on the Bitcoin bandwagon. As a sort of experiment. This means you can now pay using Bitcoins in the AdRotate Shop using regular checkout.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/bugs-blocks-broken-credit-cards/">Bugs in blocks and broken credit cards</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/i8vsT6EohbA" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/bugs-blocks-broken-credit-cards/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/bugs-blocks-broken-credit-cards/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:57:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"AdRotate Pro 3.8.14 and AdRotate Free 3.8.10";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~3/BK3Zeo5ZryQ/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/adrotate-pro-3-8-14-adrotate-free-3-8-10/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 25 Nov 2013 22:51:24 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"bugfixes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"free";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/?p=8739";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:570:"<p>Bug fix updates all around. A number of fixes have been implemented which may affect the output of your groups. Be sure to check if they still show correctly and if not make changes accordingly. A number of changes have been implemented which should impact the performance of your site a little bit, making things [&#8230;]</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/adrotate-pro-3-8-14-adrotate-free-3-8-10/">AdRotate Pro 3.8.14 and AdRotate Free 3.8.10</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Arnan de Gans";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2125:"<p>Bug fix updates all around.<br />\nA number of fixes have been implemented which may affect the output of your groups. Be sure to check if they still show correctly and if not make changes accordingly.<br />\nA number of changes have been implemented which should impact the performance of your site a little bit, making things faster! <img src=''http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Both versions have been tested to work with WP 3.7 and up.</p>\n<h3>Changes:</h3>\n<h3>AdRotate Pro 3.8.14</h3>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>[fix] Illegal string offset for weight value for some users</li>\n<li>[fix] get_plugin_data undefined for some users</li>\n<li>[fix] Output error for Geo Location in error_log</li>\n<li>[fix] Dynamic Groups now actually honor margins</li>\n<li>[fix] Dynamic Groups should no longer show all ads on pageload</li>\n<li>[fix] Faulty query calling non-existing field &#8216;schedules&#8217; on advertiser pages</li>\n<li>[change] Better size calculation for Dynamic and Block Groups</li>\n<li>[change] Clearer distinction between front-end/back-end when loading code</li>\n<li>[change] Update notification only shows for admins</li>\n<li>[new] More fine-grained control over margins in dynamic groups and blocks</li>\n</ul>\n<p></div>\n\n<h3>AdRotate Free 3.8.10</h3>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>[fix] Dynamic Groups now actually honor margins</li>\n<li>[fix] Dynamic Groups should no longer show all ads on pageload</li>\n<li>[change] Better size calculation for Dynamic and Block Groups</li>\n<li>[change] Reduced MySQL load for some ads</li>\n<li>[change] Clearer distinction between front-end/back-end when loading code</li>\n</ul>\n<p></div>\n\n<p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/adrotate-pro-3-8-14-adrotate-free-3-8-10/">AdRotate Pro 3.8.14 and AdRotate Free 3.8.10</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/BK3Zeo5ZryQ" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/adrotate-pro-3-8-14-adrotate-free-3-8-10/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/adrotate-pro-3-8-14-adrotate-free-3-8-10/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:51:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"People and their ad-blockers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~3/clwmBP9WqFc/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/people-ad-blockers/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 19 Nov 2013 10:46:30 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"adblocker";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Thoughts";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/?p=8651";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:523:"<p>Lately more often I get questions along the lines of; AdRotate doesn&#8217;t work at all, I see no ads And 8 out of 10 times it&#8217;s their ad blocker. I don&#8217;t see how such questions apply to me at all. Or even why they should be asked. You&#8217;re breaking things yourself! AdRotate is meant to [&#8230;]</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/people-ad-blockers/">People and their ad-blockers</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Arnan de Gans";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4521:"<p><img src="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/adblock-150x150.png" alt="adblock" width="150" height="150" class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-8652" />Lately more often I get questions along the lines of;</p>\n<blockquote><p>AdRotate doesn&#8217;t work at all, I see no ads</p></blockquote>\n<p>And 8 out of 10 times it&#8217;s their ad blocker.</p>\n<p>I don&#8217;t see how such questions apply to me at all. Or even why they should be asked. You&#8217;re breaking things yourself!<br />\nAdRotate is meant to Publish ads. Ad blockers are meant to remove ads. Seems like things are working just fine.</p>\n<p>Obviously I recognize the hazard ad-blockers form for your site and potential income so let&#8217;s work together here.<br />\nYou should publish less obnoxious ads so there is no reason for the ad blocker to exist.<br />\nAnd also very important stop making it easy on the ad blockers by using less distinct keywords that identify an ad.</p>\n<p>AdRotate tries to steer clear of using words that can identify code as an ad. So whatever Ad blockers think of your code is mostly your own doing by what you enter into the Adcode field of AdRotate.<br />\nThe one big and annoying exception being if you use the clicktracker. Since that will add the word &#8220;AdRotate&#8221; to the outgoing link (Because of the redirect). I haven&#8217;t yet found a way around that.</p>\n<h3>Smarter ads</h3>\n<p>When you create ads, do not use the words ad, advertisement, sponsor, promotion or such like anywhere. Not in your HTML either. For example you can create a simple ad with:</p>\n\n<div class="wp_syntax"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre class="html" style="font-family:monospace;">&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ajdg.net&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://url.to/image.jpg&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<p>That&#8217;s fairly innocent and as far as browsers and ad blockers are concerned that&#8217;s just a image that links somewhere.</p>\n<p>Should you change that to something like:</p>\n\n<div class="wp_syntax"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre class="html" style="font-family:monospace;">&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ajdg.net&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://url.to/468x60-sales-ad.jpg&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<p>Suddenly it&#8217;s an advert. Why? Because of your image file name. It tells a typical ad size 468&#215;60 and it has &#8220;ad&#8221; in the name.</p>\n<p>Another good example;</p>\n\n<div class="wp_syntax"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre class="html" style="font-family:monospace;">&lt;a class=&quot;top-head-advertisement&quot; href=&quot;http://www.ajdg.net&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://url.to/image.jpg&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<p>Why? Because you use the word &#8220;advertisement&#8221; in a CSS class.</p>\n<p>Avoid using it. Obfuscate words and things are much easier on you and your revenue stream.</p>\n<h3>Combatting ad-blockers</h3>\n<p>Technologies exist to detect ad blockers. Some sites use them and present you with an annoying popup or something. But so far I&#8217;ve seen no one use that for something useful, like showing another ad.<br />\nExample;  I use an ad blocker (Yes!) and sometimes I go to a site and see a popover thing telling me I use a ad blocker. Great. But I already knew that.<br />\nWhat&#8217;s the point&#8230; </p>\n<p>Wouldn&#8217;t it be better if that popover just showed me another ad? Why tell me something I already know. It&#8217;s still a potentially missed click that way. If instead of that message I would see another (appealing) ad or something subtle I may click after-all. Nothing is lost then. Of course this goes 2 ways.<br />\nIf I hadn&#8217;t used an ad blocker my &#8220;browse-flow&#8221; wouldn&#8217;t be disturbed by the popup so by using one I only make it difficult for myself. Meanwhile you, the advertiser, still got to show your ad.</p>\n<p>I am exploring options to circumvent ad blockers that way for a future version of AdRotate. Put that detection to good use instead of confirming my Ad blocker works.<br />\nI have no idea how to actually do it yet. But the idea and concept is there. Ready to be exploited!</p>\n<p>Thoughts?</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/people-ad-blockers/">People and their ad-blockers</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/clwmBP9WqFc" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/people-ad-blockers/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/11/people-ad-blockers/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"Do you keep your old ads in AdRotate?";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~3/I_ZpJd3rOLw/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/keep-old-ads-adrotate/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 29 Oct 2013 19:21:02 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"adverts";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"features";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"free";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/?p=8273";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:528:"<p>I&#8217;m considering a sort of archiving function for AdRotate where expired/unused ads can be moved to instead of lingering in disabled ads. But to make that useful a big question is; What do you do with your old ads? Do you re-use them? Delete them? What do you do? And if you keep them around, [&#8230;]</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/keep-old-ads-adrotate/">Do you keep your old ads in AdRotate?</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Arnan de Gans";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:714:"<p>I&#8217;m considering a sort of archiving function for AdRotate where expired/unused ads can be moved to instead of lingering in disabled ads.</p>\n<blockquote><p>But to make that useful a big question is; What do you do with your old ads?</p></blockquote>\n<p>Do you re-use them? Delete them? What do you do?<br />\nAnd if you keep them around, why do you keep them? For stats? Nostalgia?</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/keep-old-ads-adrotate/">Do you keep your old ads in AdRotate?</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/I_ZpJd3rOLw" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/keep-old-ads-adrotate/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/keep-old-ads-adrotate/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"AdRotate (Pro) ready for WordPress 3.7";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~3/y8i1CfZZrvw/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-ready-wordpress-3-7/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 26 Oct 2013 22:09:22 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Products";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"free";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/?p=8221";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:625:"<p>Initial testing indicates that all recent versions of AdRotate and AdRotate Pro are fully functional on WordPress 3.7 released yesterday. Should you run into any trouble after upgrading to WordPress 3.7, make sure you have the latest version of AdRotate installed. If that won&#8217;t solve the issue post on the forum &#8211; http://www.adrotateplugin.com/support/forums/ Users who [&#8230;]</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-ready-wordpress-3-7/">AdRotate (Pro) ready for WordPress 3.7</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Arnan de Gans";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:814:"<p>Initial testing indicates that all recent versions of AdRotate and AdRotate Pro are fully functional on WordPress 3.7 released yesterday.<br />\nShould you run into any trouble after upgrading to WordPress 3.7, make sure you have the latest version of AdRotate installed. </p>\n<p>If that won&#8217;t solve the issue post on the forum &#8211; http://www.adrotateplugin.com/support/forums/<br />\nUsers who bought AdRotate Pro can email me a Support ticket from their dashboard.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-ready-wordpress-3-7/">AdRotate (Pro) ready for WordPress 3.7</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/y8i1CfZZrvw" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-ready-wordpress-3-7/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-ready-wordpress-3-7/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"AdRotate Pro – Fixing Geo Location!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~3/6E_UFKOqECE/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-fixing-geo-location/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 23 Oct 2013 22:51:41 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"bug";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"fixed";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"geolocation";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/?p=8136";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:559:"<p>If you use Geo Location and have already updated to 3.8.12 you should update to 3.8.13 as soon as possible. A bug introduced in 3.8.12 may cause AdRotate Pro to stop getting data from Freegeoip. So the Geo Location feature doesn&#8217;t work for some users. This update resolves this issue. You may have to resave [&#8230;]</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-fixing-geo-location/">AdRotate Pro &#8211; Fixing Geo Location!</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Arnan de Gans";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1378:"<p>If you use Geo Location and have already updated to 3.8.12 you should update to 3.8.13 as soon as possible.<br />\nA bug introduced in 3.8.12 may cause AdRotate Pro to stop getting data from Freegeoip. So the Geo Location feature doesn&#8217;t work for some users.<br />\nThis update resolves this issue. You may have to resave a group for the fix to take effect.</p>\n<p>On top of that, based on some user feedback I&#8217;ve reworked the Schedule filter so it uses less MySQL queries. Reducing server load.</p>\n<h3>Changelog:</h3>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>[change] Reduced MySQL load for some ads</li>\n<li>[fix] Geo Location not fetching data for some users</li>\n</ul>\n<p></div>\n\n<p><strong>Update:</strong> There is another bug caused by the patch. Some users are affected by this when using Geo Location. A patch is being tested right now (1:15pm CET) and should be ready later today.</p>\n<p><strong>Update 2:</strong> The error has been patched and a fixed version of version 3.8.13 has been uploaded.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-fixing-geo-location/">AdRotate Pro &#8211; Fixing Geo Location!</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.adrotateplugin.com">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/6E_UFKOqECE" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-fixing-geo-location/feed/";s:7:"a